id: ER3
name: The First Regulation of G.ravity
text: |
  A pausable intent is any announcement of intent for performing a
  dependent action either without N objections, with N Agoran
  consent, with notice, or with T notice.

  G. CAN, by announcement, cause this regulation to extend the prior
  deadline, provided for in Rule 2595(3), for performing a dependent
  action based on a specified pausable intent (i.e. change the time
  between intent announcement and the enabling of the performance of
  the specified dependent action), to 14 days.
